olive oil
1 onion
1 carrot
1 packet pork mince
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet sour cream
2 clove garlic
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Finely chop garlic and onion.
Grate carrot.

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook
pork mince, onion and carrot, breaking mince up with a spoon, until just
browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and Louisiana spice blend and cook, stirring, until fragrant,
1 minute.

• Arrange mini flour tortillas over a lined oven tray. Divide pork filling
between tortillas, spooning it onto one half of each tortilla, then top with
shredded Cheddar cheese.
• Fold the empty half of each tortilla over to enclose filling and press down
with a spatula. Brush (or spray) tortillas with a drizzle of olive oil
and season.
• Bake quesadillas until cheese has melted and tortillas are golden,
10-12 minutes. Spoon any overflowing filling back into the quesadillas.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop tomato and cucumber. In a medium bowl,
combine tomato, cucumber and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive
oil. Season to taste.
• Divide Southern cheesy pork quesadillas between plates.
• Serve with cucumber salsa and a dollop of sour cream.